@node Prompt assembly
@section Prompt assembly

@findex anki-noter-prompts-build

The function @code{anki-noter-prompts-build} assembles the full system prompt sent to the LLM@.  It takes a template name, deck string, and tags string as positional arguments, plus the following keyword arguments: @code{:card-count}, @code{:language}, @code{:cite-source}, @code{:existing-cards}, and @code{:topic}. @*

The function retrieves the template text from @code{anki-noter-prompt-templates}, constructs the base prompt (which includes the output format specification, card quality guidelines, and any conditional sections for citation, card count, language, topic focus, and existing cards), and appends the template-specific instructions. @*

This function is useful if you want to build prompts programmatically for custom workflows---for example, to generate cards in batch or to inspect the prompt before sending it: @*

@lisp
(let ((prompt (anki-noter-prompts-build
               "general" "Default" "study"
               :card-count 10
               :language "Spanish"
               :cite-source "my-notes.org")))
  (message "%s" prompt))
@end lisp

